question.title: Why does VS Code think this Spring Framework import cannot be resolved?
question.body:
I'm trying to run a Java/Maven project that apparently works for others, but VS Code won't run this Spring Boot project because:

The import org.springframework.data cannot be resolved.

import org.springframework.data.repository.CrudRepository

However, my POM has the dependency that includes that class:

<dependency>
    <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
    <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-data-jpa</artifactId>
</dependency>

And the spring-boot-starter-parent the project uses is at v2.7.14.

I have the Java extension pack for VS Code.

I've tried mvn clean. There's no "reload project" option as some things have said, but I thought I read that VS Code does that when pom.xml changes, so I've tried that.

I'm sure it's something simple I'm not doing right, but I can't for the life of me figure it out.
